<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-561-738  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 561 738.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Today's Office  August 1989 v24 n3 p28(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Protect your PC against power that corrupts.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Morley, Jeanine.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Electrical variations caused by power disturbances can severelydamage microcomputers and destroy data.andP;  Power disturbances oftenresult from electrical equipment at the user's location, ratherthan outside disturbances.andP;  Power protection devices have beendeveloped to prevent such damage.andP;  There are four types ofprotectors: surge suppressors, power filters, line conditionersand uninterruptible power supplies.andP;  Surge suppressors are themost popular protective device.andP;  These devices detect power surgesand reduce the power supply according to need.andP;  Filters eliminatenoise in the line, while line conditioners remove irregularitiesin power supply.andP;  An uninterruptible power supply provides abackup for power irregularities, as well as providing a backup incase of power failure.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MicrocomputersBack-Up Power SupplyPower FailurePeripheralsAdd-In-On Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>